        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Disabled Veterans Tax Termination Act</strong></p> <p>This bill modifies provisions related to military retired pay. Specifically, the bill authorizes veterans with a service-connected disability of less than 50% to concurrently receive both retired pay and disability compensation. The bill also makes qualified disability retirees with less than 20 years of retirement-creditable service eligible for concurrent receipt, subject to specified reductions in retired pay.</p>]]>
        </text>
